'''Jetix''' was a children's television programming brand owned by [[Disney-ABC Television Group]] broadcast in [[Spain]]. It was previously known as [[Fox Kids]].
Jetix became the [[Spain | Spanish]] version of [[Disney XD (Spain)|Disney XD]] on 18 September 2009.<ref name="ocioyviajes.net">http://www.ocioyviajes.net/2009/06/nuevo-canal-disney-xd.html</ref>
==Disney XD rebrand== FOX Kids Spain began in 1998 as a replacement for [[MiniMax]] in Spain. However in April 1999, FOX Kids moved to a different channel slot because of the new Nickelodeon Spain channel.
Because Disney started owned FOX Kids in 2004, FOX Kids Spain and its other channels were rebranded as [[Jetix]].
Following the launch of [[Disney XD]] on 13 February 2009, in the US, [[Disney-ABC Television Group]] was spreading some European countries in 2009.<ref name="Disney XD"> {{cite web |url=http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/?p=14241 |title=French Jetix becomes Disney XD |publisher=Broadband TV News |date=2009-02-16 }}</ref><ref name="Disney XD2"> {{cite web |url=http://www.c21media.net/resources/detail.asp?area=79&article=47666 |title=Jetix France rebrands as Disney XD |publisher=[[C21 Media]] |date=2009-02-17 }}</ref> "[[Disney XD (Spain)|Disney XD]]" was released in Spain in September 2009.<ref name="ocioyviajes.net"/>
